00:02:15.220 --> 00:02:16.446
on math or science.

00:02:16.446 --> 00:02:18.915
And I just find it
strange because I've

00:02:18.915 --> 00:02:20.820
gone to so many countries
around the world

00:02:20.820 --> 00:02:22.462
to do firsthand research.

00:02:22.462 --> 00:02:25.450
I've gone to institutions,
libraries, and museums

00:02:25.450 --> 00:02:27.800
throughout the US,
Canada, Europe,

00:02:27.800 --> 00:02:29.394
and I'll find the
complete opposite

00:02:29.394 --> 00:02:30.810
of what's taught
in the classroom.

00:02:30.810 --> 00:02:34.080
That Africans have made
a tremendous contribution

00:02:34.080 --> 00:02:36.470
to technology and
many other fields.

00:02:36.470 --> 00:02:38.590
That's really what I'm
going to focus on today.

