01:04:38.450 --> 01:04:41.040
Even the term Ethiopia,
is a Greek term which

01:04:41.040 --> 01:04:43.230
means burnt face, blackface.

01:04:43.230 --> 01:04:44.760
or kissed by the sun.

01:04:44.760 --> 01:04:48.920
So those images that you
actually see are very accurate.

01:04:48.920 --> 01:04:52.540
The people in Sudan
and Nubians-- Nubians

01:04:52.540 --> 01:04:54.650
are in southern Egypt
and northern Sudan.

01:04:54.650 --> 01:04:57.880
You can see those
variations even today.

01:04:57.880 --> 01:04:59.690
And not only that,
but, the other one

01:04:59.690 --> 01:05:03.487
that you mentioned,
they're very specific.

01:05:03.487 --> 01:05:04.570
They're very specifically.

01:05:04.570 --> 01:05:07.160
The artists were
very, very detailed

01:05:07.160 --> 01:05:11.300
in how they portrayed
things, not only people,

01:05:11.300 --> 01:05:15.280
but they are so specific you
can see the species of plants,

01:05:15.280 --> 01:05:18.450
the species of fish,
because they were very, very

01:05:18.450 --> 01:05:20.530
detailed in how they present it.

01:05:20.530 --> 01:05:24.970
So here, when you
see-- there's better,

01:05:24.970 --> 01:05:28.810
but how the people dress,
their attire, the details,

01:05:28.810 --> 01:05:32.110
their beards, all these
things are very accurate.

01:05:32.110 --> 01:05:33.640
And this is how
we're able to tell

01:05:33.640 --> 01:05:39.240
not only from the inscriptions,
but how they're depicted.

01:05:39.240 --> 01:05:42.660
So they really didn't-- They
were not loose with how they

01:05:42.660 --> 01:05:44.090
portrayed people.

01:05:44.090 --> 01:05:46.929
But some have said these
are just generalized.

01:05:46.929 --> 01:05:47.970
They are not generalized.

01:05:47.970 --> 01:05:49.460
They are very specific.

01:05:49.460 --> 01:05:51.760
And that's why a person
goes to a museum,

01:05:51.760 --> 01:05:54.890
they can see that,
in many cases,

01:05:54.890 --> 01:05:58.960
you go to different museums,
there's no name of the person.

01:05:58.960 --> 01:06:02.140
And the location, it will
say provenance unknown.

01:06:02.140 --> 01:06:04.030
In other words,
there are assuming

01:06:04.030 --> 01:06:06.540
that this statue represents
that person because

01:06:06.540 --> 01:06:10.640
of the stylistic--
specific stylistic details.

01:06:10.640 --> 01:06:13.310
And because of that, they
say it must be this person.

01:06:13.310 --> 01:06:17.497
You see that many times, assumed
to be King such and such.

01:06:17.497 --> 01:06:19.830
And they say provenance unknown
because they don't know.

01:06:19.830 --> 01:06:22.190
They bought it from somebody.

01:06:22.190 --> 01:06:25.600
And how could they assume who
it is if they all look alike.

01:06:25.600 --> 01:06:27.680
No, it's very specific.

01:06:27.680 --> 01:06:31.540
And you can see the variations
of skin tone, dress.

01:06:31.540 --> 01:06:33.060
So that's a whole
other argument,

01:06:33.060 --> 01:06:35.422
but it's actually a
great question though.

