01:06:56.560 --> 01:07:02.030
I took out a lot of
slides, but this place here

01:07:02.030 --> 01:07:04.910
Nazlet El-Semman And
this location here,

01:07:04.910 --> 01:07:11.330
as of 1992, the Giza mapping
project led by Mark Lehner,

01:07:11.330 --> 01:07:16.830
we now know the tombs have been
found of the actual pyramid

01:07:16.830 --> 01:07:17.720
builders.

01:07:17.720 --> 01:07:20.480
We know their titles,
what days they worked,

01:07:20.480 --> 01:07:21.700
what days they had off.

01:07:21.700 --> 01:07:25.040
So they would work 7 days
and then have 3 days off.

01:07:25.040 --> 01:07:25.790
That was a week.

01:07:25.790 --> 01:07:28.220
So a week was a 10 day period.

01:07:28.220 --> 01:07:29.550
So there were 3 10 day weeks.

01:07:29.550 --> 01:07:33.160
They worked 7 days, 3 days
off, work 7 days, 3 days off,

01:07:33.160 --> 01:07:34.760
work 7 days off.

01:07:34.760 --> 01:07:37.120
We know they were paid with
grains of wheat, grains

01:07:37.120 --> 01:07:38.980
of barley, and with linen cloth.

01:07:38.980 --> 01:07:41.760
So the records were very clear
that these were paid laborers,

01:07:41.760 --> 01:07:45.020
that no one was involved
in forced labor.

01:07:45.020 --> 01:07:49.450
So the place of Nazlet
El-Semman since '91-- actually,

01:07:49.450 --> 01:07:54.240
since '92, now, the slavery
argument it has no weight.

01:07:54.240 --> 01:07:56.520
Before that, people argued
it without evidence.

01:07:56.520 --> 01:07:58.920
Now, the argument can't
be advanced anymore

01:07:58.920 --> 01:08:01.800
because of the evidence
at Nazlet El-Semman

01:08:01.800 --> 01:08:05.600
and knowing when people were
paying and how they were paid.

01:08:05.600 --> 01:08:06.469
Yeah?

01:08:06.469 --> 01:08:08.010
AUDIENCE: So there's
evidence for all

01:08:08.010 --> 01:08:09.470
the different positions?

01:08:09.470 --> 01:08:10.913
MANU AMPIM: Yes.

01:08:10.913 --> 01:08:12.746
AUDIENCE: I thought
