And so they're
pulling the stones.

01:10:00.900 --> 01:10:04.760
So they showed the
men and the ropes.

01:10:04.760 --> 01:10:07.830
And then, when I went to
Egypt a few months later,

01:10:07.830 --> 01:10:10.200
I'll learned that
what they didn't show

01:10:10.200 --> 01:10:13.750
was the tractor that was
really pulling in the stone.

01:10:13.750 --> 01:10:16.190
So this is a joke,
but nevertheless, that

01:10:16.190 --> 01:10:20.810
was because they did find the
evidence of the actual pyramid

01:10:20.810 --> 01:10:21.370
builders.

01:10:21.370 --> 01:10:24.747
Now, as I said,
that argument really

01:10:24.747 --> 01:10:26.080
doesn't have any weight anymore.

01:10:26.080 --> 01:10:28.200
But if you look up
Mark Lehner, you

01:10:28.200 --> 01:10:32.610
can actually see
some of their evidece

01:10:32.610 --> 01:10:34.720
because he's the one
that's really over the site

01:10:34.720 --> 01:10:38.540
now, Mark Lehner.

01:10:38.540 --> 01:10:42.660
But that really just
helped slay the argument.

01:10:42.660 --> 01:10:43.803
AUDIENCE: A follow up here.

01:10:43.803 --> 01:10:45.860
So there still
were slaves, right?

01:10:45.860 --> 01:10:49.100
So was there [INAUDIBLE]
edition that--

01:10:49.100 --> 01:10:51.350
who actually got
a part at the job,

01:10:51.350 --> 01:10:53.360
and then, slaves
had other roles?

01:10:53.360 --> 01:10:55.610
MANU AMPIM: Slaves.

01:10:55.610 --> 01:10:58.240
The slave idea comes
from two sources,

01:10:58.240 --> 01:11:00.866
from the biblical idea
and then some of the later

01:11:00.866 --> 01:11:02.990
Greek writers, who had no
idea how they were built,

01:11:02.990 --> 01:11:04.890
so they made up
a lot of stories.

01:11:04.890 --> 01:11:09.920
So many people think that
there were slaves in the Bible

01:11:09.920 --> 01:11:10.950
that built pyramids.

01:11:10.950 --> 01:11:14.060
The problem is the very
first Hebrew was Abraham.

01:11:14.060 --> 01:11:19.310
Abraham was dated to
about 1600 or 1650 BCE.

01:11:19.310 --> 01:11:22.840
The problem is that that's 1,000
years after these were built.

01:11:22.840 --> 01:11:25.570
So how could Abraham
leap through history,

01:11:25.570 --> 01:11:29.890
1,000 years before him,
and build pyramids?

01:11:29.890 --> 01:11:33.060
So there's no evidence
of any slaves whatsoever.

01:11:33.060 --> 01:11:35.080
What you do see
though is that when

01:11:35.080 --> 01:11:38.240
Egypt-- when other nations
tried to invade Egypt,

01:11:38.240 --> 01:11:40.530
you do see captors.

01:11:40.530 --> 01:11:42.340
You see prisoners of
war, but you never

01:11:42.340 --> 01:11:45.240
see them being employed
into any kind of labor.

01:11:45.240 --> 01:11:46.250
So you see that.

01:11:46.250 --> 01:11:47.637
You see bound captives.

01:11:47.637 --> 01:11:50.220
And then, the Greeks came around
and made up a lot of stories.

01:11:50.220 --> 01:11:53.220
Herodotus is a very good
source for Greek myth

01:11:53.220 --> 01:11:56.500
like, for example, Herodotus
is saying that-- Herodotus

01:11:56.500 --> 01:11:59.010
is a good source
because he reports what

01:11:59.010 --> 01:12:04.010
he saw at the time, at 500 BCE,
and he reports what he heard.

01:12:04.010 --> 01:12:05.827
And so Herodotus relays myths.

01:12:05.827 --> 01:12:08.160
And he said, look, I'm just
going to say what the Greeks

01:12:08.160 --> 01:12:08.680
say .

01:12:08.680 --> 01:12:10.840
So according to the
Greek mythology,

01:12:10.840 --> 01:12:16.060
Khufu-- those smaller pyramids
were built because Khufu's

01:12:16.060 --> 01:12:20.290
daughter, supposedly, was
involved with prostitution.

01:12:20.290 --> 01:12:22.290
And for every man
that she slept with,

01:12:22.290 --> 01:12:25.570
she asked that
they bring a stone.

01:12:25.570 --> 01:12:26.390
Incredible.

01:12:26.390 --> 01:12:28.379
And that this is how
the monument was built.

01:12:28.379 --> 01:12:30.170
First of all, there is
no evidence of this.

01:12:30.170 --> 01:12:30.740
This is silly.

01:12:30.740 --> 01:12:31.900
This is the king's daughter.

01:12:31.900 --> 01:12:33.210
He has tons of
wealth, so why would

01:12:33.210 --> 01:12:34.450
she need to engage in that.

01:12:34.450 --> 01:12:36.310
But it almost seems
like Herodotus

01:12:36.310 --> 01:12:38.870
is half embarrassed
by reporting this.

01:12:38.870 --> 01:12:40.940
But this is the Greek--
the Greek's made up

01:12:40.940 --> 01:12:43.040
stories for things
they didn't understand.

01:12:43.040 --> 01:12:44.330
But those are the two sources.

01:12:44.330 --> 01:12:48.610
And, of course, the
Ten Commandments

01:12:48.610 --> 01:12:51.080
and all these other things
have come out over the years.

01:12:51.080 --> 01:12:53.320
This is what has
presented to the public

01:12:53.320 --> 01:12:54.690
that there's slavery.

01:12:54.690 --> 01:12:56.445
But there is no
slavery whatsoever.

01:12:56.445 --> 01:12:57.945
I didn't say that
they were perfect.

01:12:57.945 --> 01:12:59.500
I said there's no slavery.

01:12:59.500 --> 01:13:02.870
Because all we do see
is we see captives

01:13:02.870 --> 01:13:05.500
that are bound in warfare.

01:13:05.500 --> 01:13:07.170
But there's nobody employed.

01:13:07.170 --> 01:13:08.020
There's is no text.

01:13:08.020 --> 01:13:09.380
There's no images of it.

01:13:09.380 --> 01:13:11.240
But the idea of slaves
building the pyramid,

01:13:11.240 --> 01:13:13.600
that's been in the
public mind for awhile.

01:13:13.600 --> 01:13:16.320
And then, when the evidence
was found at Nazlet El-Semman

01:13:16.320 --> 01:13:19.104
and you had people writing about
slavery, then, they say, uh-oh.

01:13:19.104 --> 01:13:20.020
The evidence is there.

01:13:20.020 --> 01:13:21.300
We'd better back up.

01:13:21.300 --> 01:13:24.230
So they backed away
from those claims.

01:13:24.230 --> 01:13:25.740
But a lot of the
specialists were

01:13:25.740 --> 01:13:28.610
the ones promoting
the slavery idea.

01:13:28.610 --> 01:13:31.220
So that's where we are.

